
Deployment Guide

💡 Critical Recommendation for Free Hosting
Since most free-tier platforms (like Render) have ephemeral file systems (your files are wiped every time the server restarts), you should:

Commit your data: Run your ingestion script locally to generate the chroma_data folder.
Upload to GitHub: Include the chroma_data folder in your Git repository. This ensures your knowledge base is "baked into" your deployment and doesn't disappear.
Deployment Checklist:

 Sign up for Neon.tech and get your PostgreSQL connection string.
 Push your code to GitHub (including the pre-indexed chroma_data if applicable).
 Connect your repo to Render (Backend) and Vercel (Frontend).
 Add your .env variables to their respective dashboards.
Would you like help with anything else, like setting up the deployment scripts or troubleshooting the database connection?

